metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #305
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

metadata.name: Fronteras en abstracto #214
metadata.description:
A place in the abstract, walking in one direction without knowing if you will reach that place. Then, in case you find it, go to the other side before dawn.

It's just a game of words and phrases that have to be given meaning, and we find it on the frontier of something that we don't know what it is.

//

Un lugar en abstracto, caminando en una dirección sin saber si se llega a ese lugar. Luego, en caso de encontrarlo, pasar al otro lado antes del amanecer.

Es solo un juego de palabras y frases a las cuales hay que darles sentido, y lo encontramos en la frontera de algo que no sabemos qué es.

//


Keys

[s] -> download still image (in live view)
[1,2,3,4] Pixel ratios

metadata.name: Layered Landscapes #64
metadata.description:
Layered Landscapes explores representing imaginary landscapes through line art designed for output with a pen plotter.

It supports these variations:

Hill Contours: 4 layers
Dark Foreground: 50% chance the first contour is overprinted for darker darks
Sky: straight or curved
fog: 0, 1 or 2 layers
trees: 1 to 7

Press "s" to download the SVG.

Output is designed for 6" x 4".

metadata.name: Retroscapes #95
metadata.description:
You are approaching newly discovered planetary ring system, seen by no human before.
Gravity works in strange ways there. Intrigued, you grab your polaroid. 
Snap, and there it is - your grainy Retroscape.

Beauty comes from diversity.

Size of the collection - 222 pieces - is a tribute to my first NFT.

metadata.name: Mindset #12
metadata.description:
Creating concepts implies creating limits in the continuous. 
Definitions are necessary to communicate. 
Boundaries have to be set to be broken.
Beliefs define our ego but not our essence.
Aren't we the invisible structure that can perceive itself under its own construct?



"QWERTY" Camera selection
"A" Automatic rotation (in perspective view)
"Click & Drag" Manual Rotation (in perspective view)
"Mouse Wheel" Camera distance (in perspective view)
"X" Export PNG Menu (in live mode)

Created with p5.js by Victor Doval @vicdoval (2022)
Designed to be seen in Google Chrome 97.0.4692.99

metadata.name: Action Fields #8
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: Yellow House #183
metadata.description:
It is very easy to forget the beauty of the places we consume because they are available to us by nature.
The things we consume all our lives we find not so special.
It’s very hard to remember how special and valuable these things really are.

With this work, I will try to give sincere admiration and respect to my favorite place on the beach!

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 'f' to save .png with resolution = 4000px x 4000px

Created using p5js ,100% p5.js code and math.

@Mutart, April, 2022.

metadata.name: Negative Space #218
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #192
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Ornithic #79
metadata.description:
Pure p5.js code. No svg, no image, no other materials. Creating code arts with polar coordinate system and algorithms are my passion. This generative art contains a lot of features that may be rare than common.  

• 30 color palettes // 2 of them have 3 different colors
• 4 grass structures // With the same algorithm 
• 16 flower types //  Count, leaf number and size
• 6 color functions // Different colorizations with b&w 

Also, the outputs of the project are very high resolution to print or something like that.
April / 2022
Rhaegar

metadata.name: Sap song #40
metadata.description:
This audiovisual generative artwork proposes sonorous green forms that flow excessively. Frenetic arpeggios and populations of plants are emerging, organized in their own way. And the sap sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. “Enredo coral”
II. “Recitativo libre”
III. “Coda hacia la raíz”

Original cello, marimba and music box samplers.

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

attributes.name: Information
attributes.value: Dark tidy green version, in D minor mode, for choir of 50 voices/plants.

metadata.name: Refractions #22
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective
